<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-08-1226 </DOCNO><TEXT>In its current state of development the programmable Multispectral Imageroffers a number of advantages over conventional forest damage monitoringtechniques and instruments. High spectral resolution, digital format,automatic interpretation, computer-generated maps, early detection ofdamage are examples and it is expected that the imager will be able togenerate forest damage maps in real time in the future. (Refs. 1).</TEXT></DOC>